1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,600
You don't realize how convenient a Front-Opening Design is until you put one in your trunk. With half-opening luggage, there's no quick access, you have to lay the whole thing flat just to grab one item. It takes up space, and stuff spills everywhere. This Front-Opening Design? Zero hassle. It opens lying down OR standing up, and everything's right there.

2
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:24,600
The shallow compartment holds your everyday essentials, power bank, cables, laptop. Grab whatever you need, and your trunk stays perfectly organized. And here's the best part, it also opens like THIS...

3
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:42,500
...so pulling out a jacket takes two seconds. And don't worry about capacity. Down here is the spacious deep compartment, totally different from an Equal Split Design. With half-opening luggage, you're constantly balancing both sides, and bulky stuff just doesn't fit. This deep compartment loads straight down, coats, boots, big bags, just press them right in. It packs full AND closes easy, it maximizes every inch of space, giving you 20% more than an Equal Split Design.

4
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:52,100
Every wheel is a high-rebound T-P-E wheel with its own shock-absorbing spring. Even fully loaded, it rolls just as smooth, and just as quiet.

5
00:00:52,100 --> 00:01:02,800
There's a cup holder on the side, perfect for your water or coffee while you wait. Plus a 66-watt fast-charging port, so your phone charges while you walk.

6
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:13,500
The handle even has a hook, hang a hat, a shopping bag, whatever. It holds your phone too. But honestly? My favorite thing about this luggage is that it just feels... alive. Like it was actually designed by someone who travels.
